A Nigerian lady residing in Canada has posed some vital questions to her countrymen who have declared readiness to relocate abroad by all means.
She asked if Nigerians are ready to cope with the cold in places like Canada and other countries where snow falls.
The woman also asked if they are ready to experience racism, loneliness, lockdown and even pay the high taxes imposed on residents and citizens.
She shared a clip of herself in snow while asking the questions in a caption format.
”You want to come to Canada right? You wanna come chill with us??
Ae you ready for the cold, racism, taxes, loneliness, lockdown”, she wrote.
